    <div class="documentTop">        
        
        <h1>Department for Nature Management</h1>
        
        <div class="pageDescription"><font face="DepMyriadRegular" size="1">
<p align="left">The department is responsible for development of policy and strategies and administrative tasks related to protection and sustainable use of biological diversity and outdoor recreation. Major areas in nature management are implementation of plans for protected areas (including protection of coniferous forests, the National Park Plan, country protection plans, and marine and coastal protection plans), management of predators and other wildlife, management of watercourses, evaluation of environmental aspects of agriculture, forestry and fisheries, evaluation of consequences related to import and use of GMO’s, as well as other environmental effects of biotechnology, motorised transport and supervision of natural areas. In addition the department is responsible for Norway’s participation in the UN Convention on Biological Diversity and the Carthagena Protocol on GMO’s, Norway’s participation in international environmental cooperation related to forestry, NASCO and other international conventions concerning biological diversity.</p></font></div>        
